long_desc.thetext:
In qx.ui.mobile.container.MIScroll mixin (qx.mobile.nativescroll=false) , onBeforeCallStart iScroll option calls preventDefault() on most of native events unless they are triggered from certain dom element types, i.e. :


        onBeforeScrollStart : function(e) {
...
          if (target.tagName != 'SELECT' && target.tagName != 'INPUT' && target.tagName != 'TEXTAREA' && target.tagName != 'LABEL') {
...
            e.preventDefault();
...
        }

This prevents all sorts of native events to be trigerred, e.g. hyperlinks navigation.

Simply commenting the line solves the problem, but it introduces some other mis-behaviour in scrolling (both native and emulated scroll are triggered simultaneously), so it's not a solution.

As for the hyperlinks problems, it can be solved by adding "&& target.tagName != 'A'" in the exclusion condition, but this is again too restrictive.
A good solution would be to call preventDefault() on events that would actually trigger the emulated scrolling but I couldn't find a discriminator.

The issue doe not reproduce with qx.mobile.nativescroll=true
